#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.62:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga "
msgstr "6. Ignorance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 62. Dutiyasabbupādānapariyādānasutta → pariyādinnaṃ 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Dutiyasabbupādānapariyādānasutta "
msgstr "62. The Depletion of All Fuel (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.62:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbupādānapariyādānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for depleting all fuel. "

msgctxt "sn35.62:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:1.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo? "
msgstr "And what is the principle for depleting all fuel? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.62:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.62:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.62:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.62:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.62:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.62:6.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.62:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.62:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.62:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā … pe … "
msgstr "“Sights … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:8.2"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "eye consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:8.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.62:10.1"
msgid "“Cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti? "
msgstr "eye contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.62:11.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.62:12.1"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.62:13.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.62:14.1"
msgid "“Sotaṃ … "
msgstr "“Ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.2"
msgid "ghānaṃ … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.3"
msgid "jivhā … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.4"
msgid "kāyo … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.5"
msgid "mano … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.6"
msgid "dhammā … "
msgstr "thoughts … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.7"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "mind consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.8"
msgid "manosamphasso … "
msgstr "mind contact … "

msgctxt "sn35.62:14.9"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.62:15.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.62:16.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "sn35.62:17.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn35.62:18.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.62:18.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "sn35.62:19.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.35, sc20
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati. "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.62:20.2"
msgid "Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.3"
msgid "jivhāyapi nibbindati, rasesupi nibbindati, jivhāviññāṇepi nibbindati, jivhāsamphassepi nibbindati, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.4"
msgid "manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.62:20.5"
msgid "Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.62:20.6"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.7"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo”ti. "
msgstr "This is the principle for depleting all fuel.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.62:20.10"
msgid "Avijjāvaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "sn35.62:21.1"
msgid "Avijjā saṃyojanā dve, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.62:21.2"
msgid "āsavena duve vuttā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.62:21.3"
msgid "Anusayā apare dve, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.62:21.4"
msgid "pariññā dve pariyādinnaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.62:21.5"
msgid "Vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
